{{Infobox person | name = Alfred Akirov | image = Alfred Akirov.jpg | image_size = | caption = Alfred Akirov | birth_name = | birth_date = 1941 | birth_place = [[Iraq]] | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | residence = | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | alma mater = | employer = | occupation = Businessman | title = | salary = | networth = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = | box_width = }} '''Alfred Akirov''' ({{lang-he|אלפרד אקירוב}}), born in Iraq in 1941, is an Israeli businessman. He is the founder of the [[Alrov Group]].
==Early life== Alfred Akirov was born in 1941 in Iraq.<ref name="israelvalley">[http://www.israelvalley.com/news/2013/12/15/42019/legion-d-honneur-pour-alfred-akirov-ex-president-de-la-chambre-de-commerce-israel-france-2010-a-2012 Légion d'Honneur pour Alfred Akirov, ex-Président de la Chambre de Commerce Israël-France (2010 à 2012).], French-Israel Chamber of Commerce</ref> He emigrated to [[Israel]] with his family in 1953.<ref name="israelvalley" />
==Career== Akirov founded the [[Alrov Group]] in 1978<ref name="israelvalley" /><ref name="bloombergbusiness">[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=27060492&ticker=ALRPR:IT Alfred Akirov], ''Bloomberg Business''</ref> and he is currently its CEO.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bloomberg|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=27060492&privcapId=20332957|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref> It has been listed on the [[Tel Aviv Stock Exchange]] since 1983.<ref name="israelvalley" /> He helped rebuild [[Mamilla]].<ref name="israelvalley"/>
Akirov served as the President of the French-Israeli Chamber of Commerce from 2010 to 2012.<ref name="israelvalley"/> He became a Knight of the French [[Legion of Honour]] in 2013.<ref name="israelvalley" />
==Philanthropy== Akirov serves on the Board of Governors of [[Tel Aviv University]].<ref>[https://english.tau.ac.il/tau_governors_roll Tel Aviv University Governors Roll]</ref>
