The '''[http://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/taxation/company_tax/transfer_pricing/forum/ EU Joint Transfer Pricing Forum]''' (EUJTPF) was set up in 2002 from an [[European Union|EU]] [[communique|communication]]<ref>http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=COM:2001:0582:FIN:EN:PDF</ref> on eliminating [[transfer pricing]] from the EU (in which it was called the "Joint Forum on Transfer Pricing"). It was to be composed of "Member [[Nation|States]] and business representatives".

The business (non-government) members of the [[Forum (legal)|forum]] (as of 6 Oct 2013) comprises 16 people <ref>http://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/taxation/company_tax/transfer_pricing/forum/</ref> Eight of these are transfer pricing [[advisor]]s (including the Chair), and eight are [[tax]] specialists in [[Multinational corporation|multinational]]s.

