{{Use Indian English|date=February 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox company | logo = [[File:Federation of Indian Micro and Small & Medium Enterprises (FISME).jpg|Federation of Indian Micro and Small & Medium Enterprises (FISME)]] | name = The Federation of Indian Micro and Small & Medium Enterprises (FISME) | founded = 1995 | locations = 5 | location_city = [[New Delhi]] | location_country = India | key_people = D. Gandhikumar, President | homepage = {{URL|http://www.fisme.org.in}} |}}
The '''Federation of Indian Micro and Small & Medium Enterprises''' (FISME) is an [[India]]n [[NGO]] that is the progressive face of Indian MSMEs and is regarded as such by the [[Government of India]]. It is a member of the National MSME Board formed under the MSME Act 2006. FISME is consulted by SME policy making set-up of the country and also works in close coordination with the Ministry of Micro, Small & Medium Enterprises as well as major multilateral and bilateral bodies in India such as [[UNIDO]], [[ILO]], [[UNCTAD]], [[DFID]], [[GTZ]] etc. Supported by [[UNCTAD]], [[DFID]] and Ministry of Commerce & Industry, as a Tier-I partner, FISME is leading 22 provincial [[Small and medium enterprises|SME]] bodies in 18 states.<ref>(6 June 2012.) [http://www.businessworld.in/en/storypage/-/bw/ftp-needs-strategic-thrust-for-success-fisme/417056.0/page/0 "FTP Needs Strategic Thrust For Success: FISME."] Businessworld Magazine.</ref>
==History== Coinciding with the launch of major policy and support initiatives of the Indian government to promote the growth and development of small scale industries in India, FISME was initially born as the National Alliance of Young Entrepreneurs (NAYE) in 1967 to provide an outreach and advocacy forum for small industries in particular and entrepreneurship in general. In the post-liberalisation era, NAYE along with eight state level associations formed FISME in 1995.<ref>Kapur, Bhawna (8 August 2012). [http://www.businessworld.in/en/storypage/-/bw/ftp-needs-strategic-thrust-for-success-fisme/417056.0/page/0 "FISME jointly organised India SME Forum in Gurgaon."] Businessworld Magazine.</ref>
==Events== FISME conducts regular events across India catering to the different needs of SMEs. They recently conducted India SME forum recently in participation with other organisations.<ref>[http://www.aajkikhabar.com/en/News/Business/FISME-jointly-organised-India-SME-Forum-in-Gurgaon/700186.html "FISME jointly organised India SME Forum in Gurgaon."] Aajki Khabar online news portal</ref>
