{{Infobox person | name = Hicham El Amrani | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1979|3|29}} | birth_place = [[Casablanca]], [[Morocco]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = Moroccan | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = }}
'''Hicham El Amrani''' is the General Secretary of the [[Confederation of African Football]]. He was appointed in September 2011 and served until 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hicham El Amrani confirmed as CAF Secretary General|url=http://www.cafonline.com/football/news/11532-hicham-el-amrani-confirmed-as-caf-secretary-general.html|publisher=CAFonline.com|accessdate=29 September 2011|date=28 September 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Morocco's Amrani gets Caf top job|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/15109421.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=29 September 2011|date=29 September 2011}}</ref>
El Amrani succeeded Egyptian [[Mustapha Fahmy]] in the position which he had held for 28 years, initially as an interim solution in October 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Moroccan Amrani replaces Fahmy|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/9028223.stm|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=29 September 2011|date=23 September 2010}}</ref> On 26 March 2017, he resigned from the position after serving for eight years without giving any reasons for his decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingfut.com/2017/03/26/hicham-el-amrani-resigns/|title=CAF secretary general Hicham El Amrani resigns|publisher=Kingfut.com}}</ref>
Previously he had worked for the [[Asian Football Confederation]] and was involved with marketing of their competitions.
