{{Infobox Institute |name= Institute of Public Administration New Zealand |established= |chairman= |head_label= President |head=[[Jo Cribb]] |staff= 5 |budget= |debt= |location= [[Wellington, New Zealand]] |address=Level 3, Rutherford House, Pipitea Campus, Victoria University, Wellington |website= http://www.ipanz.org.nz/ }}
The '''Institute of Public Administration New Zealand''' ('''IPANZ''') is a voluntary [[public administration]] organisation. IPANZ states their goal is to :''"promoting improvements in public policy and in administration and management in the public sector in New Zealand, and to increasing public understanding of the work undertaken in the public sector"''.<ref>[http://www.ipanz.org.nz/Site/About_Us/Default.aspx IPANZ website]</ref>
IPANZ publish a quarterly journal called ''Public Sector'' and run annual awards for the [[State sector organisations in New Zealand|New Zealand public sector]] called the ''IPANZ GEN-I Public Sector Excellence Awards''.
==History== The "Public Service Administration Society" originated in [[Christchurch]] in 1934. Similar societies subsequently established (in Wellington, Auckland and Dunedin) then merged in 1936 to form the New Zealand Institute of Public Administration.<ref> {{cite book | last = Martin | first = John R. | title = Spirit of Service: A History of the Institute of Public Administration New Zealand, 1936-2006 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=bUKOAAAAMAAJ | accessdate = 2013-07-30 | year = 2006 | publisher = Institute of Public Administration New Zealand | isbn = 9780473111519 | pages = 200 }} </ref>
