'''Zvonimir Mršić''' (born 9 January 1966) is a [[Croatia]]n manager, [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of food company [[Podravka]] and a former member of the [[Croatian Parliament]].

Mršić was born in [[Koprivnica]]. He graduated from the Faculty of Political Science of the [[University of Zagreb]] in 1990.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.belupo.hr/Default.aspx?sid=11124 |title=Board of Management |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Belupo Inc. |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> He is a member of the [[Social Democratic Party of Croatia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meetdocs/2009_2014/documents/d-hr/dv/0316_02/0316_02en.pdf |title=Croatian Delegation to the EU-Croatia Joint Parliamentary Committee 2010. |author= |date=2010 |work= |publisher=European Parliament |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> From 1997 to 1999 Mršić was deputy mayor and from 2001 to 2012 mayor of Koprivnica. He was a member of parliament from 22 December 2003 to 24 February 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sabor.hr/Default.aspx?sec=4784 |title=Members of the 7th Parliament |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Croatian Parliament |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> In 2012 Mršić was appointed CEO of Podravka.

